Attributes._Description: "This is MTV coverage that can replace the last Legacy coverage."

"At this point we know we're on a MTV row and we know the previous row in a Legacy row.  If the current row fully consumes the previous row - meaning the effective date of the current row is less than or equal to the previous row and the end date of the current row is greater than or equal to the end date of the previous row - then we know the previous row is not important to us.  We can replace it with the current row.  MTV always wins."
